#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:5
msgid "NumPy 1.22.0 Release Notes"
msgstr "NumPy 1.22.0 發行備註"

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:6
msgid ""
"NumPy 1.22.0 is a big release featuring the work of 153 contributors spread "
"over 609 pull requests. There have been many improvements, highlights are:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:9
msgid ""
"Annotations of the main namespace are essentially complete. Upstream is a "
"moving target, so there will likely be further improvements, but the major "
"work is done. This is probably the most user visible enhancement in this "
"release."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:13
msgid ""
"A preliminary version of the proposed Array-API is provided. This is a step "
"in creating a standard collection of functions that can be used across "
"applications such as CuPy and JAX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:16
msgid ""
"NumPy now has a DLPack backend. DLPack provides a common interchange format "
"for array (tensor) data."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:18
msgid ""
"New methods for ``quantile``, ``percentile``, and related functions. The new "
"methods provide a complete set of the methods commonly found in the "
"literature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:21
msgid ""
"The universal functions have been refactored to implement most of :ref:`NEP "
"43 <NEP43>`.  This also unlocks the ability to experiment with the future "
"DType API."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:24
msgid "A new configurable allocator for use by downstream projects."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:26
msgid ""
"These are in addition to the ongoing work to provide SIMD support for "
"commonly used functions, improvements to F2PY, and better documentation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:29
msgid ""
"The Python versions supported in this release are 3.8-3.10, Python 3.7 has "
"been dropped. Note that the Mac wheels are now based on OS X 10.14 rather "
"than 10.9 that was used in previous NumPy release cycles. 10.14 is the "
"oldest release supported by Apple. Also note that 32 bit wheels are only "
"provided for Python 3.8 and 3.9 on Windows, all other wheels are 64 bits on "
"account of Ubuntu, Fedora, and other Linux distributions dropping 32 bit "
"support. All 64 bit wheels are also linked with 64 bit integer OpenBLAS, "
"which should fix the occasional problems encountered by folks using truly "
"huge arrays."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:40
msgid "Expired deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:43
msgid "Deprecated numeric style dtype strings have been removed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:44
msgid ""
"Using the strings ``\"Bytes0\"``, ``\"Datetime64\"``, ``\"Str0\"``, "
"``\"Uint32\"``, and ``\"Uint64\"`` as a dtype will now raise a ``TypeError``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:47
msgid "(`gh-19539 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19539>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:50
msgid ""
"Expired deprecations for ``loads``, ``ndfromtxt``, and ``mafromtxt`` in npyio"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:51
msgid ""
"``numpy.loads`` was deprecated in v1.15, with the recommendation that users "
"use ``pickle.loads`` instead.  ``ndfromtxt`` and ``mafromtxt`` were both "
"deprecated in v1.17 - users should use ``numpy.genfromtxt`` instead with the "
"appropriate value for the ``usemask`` parameter."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:56
msgid "(`gh-19615 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19615>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:60
msgid "Deprecations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:63
msgid "Use delimiter rather than delimitor as kwarg in mrecords"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:64
msgid ""
"The misspelled keyword argument ``delimitor`` of ``numpy.ma.mrecords."
"fromtextfile()`` has been changed to ``delimiter``, using it will emit a "
"deprecation warning."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:68
msgid "(`gh-19921 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19921>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:71
msgid "Passing boolean ``kth`` values to (arg-)partition has been deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:72
msgid ""
"``numpy.partition`` and ``numpy.argpartition`` would previously accept "
"boolean values for the ``kth`` parameter, which would subsequently be "
"converted into integers. This behavior has now been deprecated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:76
msgid "(`gh-20000 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/20000>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:79
msgid "The ``np.MachAr`` class has been deprecated"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:80
msgid ""
"The ``numpy.MachAr`` class and ``finfo.machar <numpy.finfo>`` attribute have "
"been deprecated. Users are encouraged to access the property if interest "
"directly from the corresponding ``numpy.finfo`` attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:84
msgid "(`gh-20201 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/20201>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:88
msgid "Compatibility notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:91
msgid "Distutils forces strict floating point model on clang"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:92
msgid ""
"NumPy now sets the ``-ftrapping-math`` option on clang to enforce correct "
"floating point error handling for universal functions.  Clang defaults to "
"non-IEEE and C99 conform behaviour otherwise.  This change (using the "
"equivalent but newer ``-ffp-exception-behavior=strict``) was attempted in "
"NumPy 1.21, but was effectively never used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:98
msgid "(`gh-19479 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19479>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:101
msgid "Removed floor division support for complex types"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:102
msgid "Floor division of complex types will now result in a ``TypeError``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:104
msgid ""
">>> a = np.arange(10) + 1j* np.arange(10)\n"
">>> a // 1\n"
"TypeError: ufunc 'floor_divide' not supported for the input types..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:110
msgid "(`gh-19135 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19135>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:113
msgid ""
"``numpy.vectorize`` functions now produce the same output class as the base "
"function"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:114
msgid ""
"When a function that respects ``numpy.ndarray`` subclasses is vectorized "
"using ``numpy.vectorize``, the vectorized function will now be subclass-safe "
"also for cases that a signature is given (i.e., when creating a ``gufunc``): "
"the output class will be the same as that returned by the first call to the "
"underlying function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:120
msgid "(`gh-19356 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19356>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:123
msgid "Python 3.7 is no longer supported"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:124
msgid ""
"Python support has been dropped. This is rather strict, there are changes "
"that require Python >= 3.8."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:127
msgid "(`gh-19665 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19665>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:130
msgid "str/repr of complex dtypes now include space after punctuation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:131
msgid ""
"The repr of ``np.dtype({\"names\": [\"a\"], \"formats\": [int], \"offsets\": "
"[2]})`` is now ``dtype({'names': ['a'], 'formats': ['<i8'], 'offsets': [2], "
"'itemsize': 10})``, whereas spaces where previously omitted after colons and "
"between fields."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:136
msgid ""
"The old behavior can be restored via ``np."
"set_printoptions(legacy=\"1.21\")``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:138
msgid "(`gh-19687 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19687>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:141
msgid "Corrected ``advance`` in ``PCG64DSXM`` and ``PCG64``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:142
msgid ""
"Fixed a bug in the ``advance`` method of ``PCG64DSXM`` and ``PCG64``. The "
"bug only affects results when the step was larger than :math:`2^{64}` on "
"platforms that do not support 128-bit integers(e.g., Windows and 32-bit "
"Linux)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:146
msgid "(`gh-20049 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/20049>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:149
msgid "Change in generation of random 32 bit floating point variates"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:150
msgid ""
"There was bug in the generation of 32 bit floating point values from the "
"uniform distribution that would result in the least significant bit of the "
"random variate always being 0.  This has been fixed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:154
msgid ""
"This change affects the variates produced by the ``random.Generator`` "
"methods ``random``, ``standard_normal``, ``standard_exponential``, and "
"``standard_gamma``, but only when the dtype is specified as ``numpy."
"float32``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:158
msgid "(`gh-20314 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/20314>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:162
msgid "C API changes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:165
msgid "Masked inner-loops cannot be customized anymore"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:166
msgid ""
"The masked inner-loop selector is now never used.  A warning will be given "
"in the unlikely event that it was customized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:169
msgid ""
"We do not expect that any code uses this.  If you do use it, you must unset "
"the selector on newer NumPy version.  Please also contact the NumPy "
"developers, we do anticipate providing a new, more specific, mechanism."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:173
msgid ""
"The customization was part of a never-implemented feature to allow for "
"faster masked operations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:176
msgid "(`gh-19259 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19259>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:179
msgid "Experimental exposure of future DType and UFunc API"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:180
msgid ""
"The new header ``experimental_public_dtype_api.h`` allows to experiment with "
"future API for improved universal function and especially user DType "
"support. At this time it is advisable to experiment using the development "
"version of NumPy since some changes are expected and new features will be "
"unlocked."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:185
msgid "(`gh-19919 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19919>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:189
msgid "New Features"
msgstr "新功能"

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:192
msgid "NEP 49 configurable allocators"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:193
msgid ""
"As detailed in `NEP 49`_, the function used for allocation of the data "
"segment of a ndarray can be changed. The policy can be set globally or in a "
"context. For more information see the NEP and the :ref:`data_memory` "
"reference docs. Also add a ``NUMPY_WARN_IF_NO_MEM_POLICY`` override to warn "
"on dangerous use of transfering ownership by setting ``NPY_ARRAY_OWNDATA``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:201
msgid "(`gh-17582 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/17582>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:204
msgid "Implementation of the NEP 47 (adopting the array API standard)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:205
msgid ""
"An initial implementation of `NEP 47`_ (adoption the array API standard) has "
"been added as ``numpy.array_api``. The implementation is experimental and "
"will issue a UserWarning on import, as the `array API standard <https://data-"
"apis.org/array-api/latest/index.html>`_ is still in draft state. ``numpy."
"array_api`` is a conforming implementation of the array API standard, which "
"is also minimal, meaning that only those functions and behaviors that are "
"required by the standard are implemented (see the NEP for more info). "
"Libraries wishing to make use of the array API standard are encouraged to "
"use ``numpy.array_api`` to check that they are only using functionality that "
"is guaranteed to be present in standard conforming implementations."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:218
msgid "(`gh-18585 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/18585>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:221
msgid ""
"Generate C/C++ API reference documentation from comments blocks is now "
"possible"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:222
msgid ""
"This feature depends on Doxygen_ in the generation process and on Breathe_ "
"to integrate it with Sphinx."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:228
msgid "(`gh-18884 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/18884>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:231
msgid "Assign the platform-specific ``c_intp`` precision via a mypy plugin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:232
msgid ""
"The mypy_ plugin, introduced in `numpy/numpy#17843`_, has again been "
"expanded: the plugin now is now responsible for setting the platform-"
"specific precision of ``numpy.ctypeslib.c_intp``, the latter being used as "
"data type for various ``numpy.ndarray.ctypes`` attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:237
msgid ""
"Without the plugin, aforementioned type will default to ``ctypes.c_int64``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:239
msgid ""
"To enable the plugin, one must add it to their mypy `configuration file`_:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:241
msgid ""
"[mypy]\n"
"plugins = numpy.typing.mypy_plugin"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:251
msgid "(`gh-19062 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19062>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:254
msgid "Add NEP 47-compatible dlpack support"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:255
msgid ""
"Add a ``ndarray.__dlpack__()`` method which returns a ``dlpack`` C structure "
"wrapped in a ``PyCapsule``. Also add a ``np._from_dlpack(obj)`` function, "
"where ``obj`` supports ``__dlpack__()``, and returns an ``ndarray``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:259
msgid "(`gh-19083 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19083>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:262
msgid ""
"``keepdims`` optional argument added to ``numpy.argmin``, ``numpy.argmax``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:263
msgid ""
"``keepdims`` argument is added to ``numpy.argmin``, ``numpy.argmax``.  If "
"set to ``True``, the axes which are reduced are left in the result as "
"dimensions with size one.  The resulting array has the same number of "
"dimensions and will broadcast with the input array."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:268
msgid "(`gh-19211 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19211>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:271
msgid "``bit_count`` to compute the number of 1-bits in an integer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:272
msgid ""
"Computes the number of 1-bits in the absolute value of the input. This works "
"on all the numpy integer types. Analogous to the builtin ``int.bit_count`` "
"or ``popcount`` in C++."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:276
msgid ""
">>> np.uint32(1023).bit_count()\n"
"10\n"
">>> np.int32(-127).bit_count()\n"
"7"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:283
msgid "(`gh-19355 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19355>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:286
msgid ""
"The ``ndim`` and ``axis`` attributes have been added to ``numpy.AxisError``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:287
msgid ""
"The ``ndim`` and ``axis`` parameters are now also stored as attributes "
"within each ``numpy.AxisError`` instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:290
msgid "(`gh-19459 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19459>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:293
msgid "Preliminary support for ``windows/arm64`` target"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:294
msgid ""
"``numpy`` added support for windows/arm64 target. Please note ``OpenBLAS`` "
"support is not yet available for windows/arm64 target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:297
msgid "(`gh-19513 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19513>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:300
msgid "Added support for LoongArch"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:301
msgid ""
"LoongArch is a new instruction set, numpy compilation failure on LoongArch "
"architecture, so add the commit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:304
msgid "(`gh-19527 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19527>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:307
msgid "A ``.clang-format`` file has been added"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:308
msgid ""
"Clang-format is a C/C++ code formatter, together with the added ``.clang-"
"format`` file, it produces code close enough to the NumPy C_STYLE_GUIDE for "
"general use. Clang-format version 12+ is required due to the use of several "
"new features, it is available in Fedora 34 and Ubuntu Focal among other "
"distributions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:314
msgid "(`gh-19754 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19754>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:317
msgid ""
"``is_integer`` is now available to ``numpy.floating`` and ``numpy.integer``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:318
msgid ""
"Based on its counterpart in Python ``float`` and ``int``, the numpy floating "
"point and integer types now support ``float.is_integer``. Returns ``True`` "
"if the number is finite with integral value, and ``False`` otherwise."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:322
msgid ""
">>> np.float32(-2.0).is_integer()\n"
"True\n"
">>> np.float64(3.2).is_integer()\n"
"False\n"
">>> np.int32(-2).is_integer()\n"
"True"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:331
msgid "(`gh-19803 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19803>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:334
msgid "Symbolic parser for Fortran dimension specifications"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:335
msgid ""
"A new symbolic parser has been added to f2py in order to correctly parse "
"dimension specifications. The parser is the basis for future improvements "
"and provides compatibility with Draft Fortran 202x."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:339
msgid "(`gh-19805 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19805>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:342
msgid "``ndarray``, ``dtype`` and ``number`` are now runtime-subscriptable"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:343
msgid ""
"Mimicking :pep:`585`, the ``numpy.ndarray``, ``numpy.dtype`` and ``numpy."
"number`` classes are now subscriptable for python 3.9 and later. "
"Consequently, expressions that were previously only allowed in .pyi stub "
"files or with the help of ``from __future__ import annotations`` are now "
"also legal during runtime."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:349
msgid ""
">>> import numpy as np\n"
">>> from typing import Any\n"
"\n"
">>> np.ndarray[Any, np.dtype[np.float64]]\n"
"numpy.ndarray[typing.Any, numpy.dtype[numpy.float64]]"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:357
msgid "(`gh-19879 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19879>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:361
msgid "Improvements"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:364
msgid "``ctypeslib.load_library`` can now take any path-like object"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:365
msgid ""
"All parameters in the can now take any :term:`python:path-like object`. This "
"includes the likes of strings, bytes and objects implementing the :meth:"
"`__fspath__<os.PathLike.__fspath__>` protocol."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:369
msgid "(`gh-17530 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/17530>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:372
msgid ""
"Add ``smallest_normal`` and ``smallest_subnormal`` attributes to ``finfo``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:373
msgid ""
"The attributes ``smallest_normal`` and ``smallest_subnormal`` are available "
"as an extension of ``finfo`` class for any floating-point data type. To use "
"these new attributes, write ``np.finfo(np.float64).smallest_normal`` or ``np."
"finfo(np.float64).smallest_subnormal``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:378
msgid "(`gh-18536 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/18536>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:381
msgid "``numpy.linalg.qr`` accepts stacked matrices as inputs"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:382
msgid ""
"``numpy.linalg.qr`` is able to produce results for stacked matrices as "
"inputs. Moreover, the implementation of QR decomposition has been shifted to "
"C from Python."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:386
msgid "(`gh-19151 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19151>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:389
msgid "``numpy.fromregex`` now accepts ``os.PathLike`` implementations"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:390
msgid ""
"``numpy.fromregex`` now accepts objects implementing the ``__fspath__<os."
"PathLike>`` protocol, *e.g.* ``pathlib.Path``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:393
msgid "(`gh-19680 <https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/19680>`__)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:396
msgid "Add new methods for ``quantile`` and ``percentile``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../release/1.22.0-notes.rst:397
msgid ""
"``quantile`` and ``percentile`` now have have a ``method=`` keyword argument "
"supporting 13 different methods.  This replaces the ``interpolation=`` "
"keyword argument."
msgstr ""

